snippet.textDisplay:
Just another day where YouTube comments remind me how so many people like to comment when they really understand very little about the efforts taken to make something actually good. Explains a lot. 😂 There would be a lot more successes if people worked as hard to create something of actual value as much as they work hard to critique the work of others, especially work that is already resplendent with value...

I'm glad to see it. It's reassuringly consistent. And if some things really in the end haven't mattered that much, it's good to know that those things will likely not continue to matter all that much as long as you have a perspective that learns not to overvalue stuff that doesn't matter that much...
